sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy
    participant Notebook as Notebook Pod<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant PyPI as PyPI Index<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Git as Git Repository<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+

    Note over User,Git: Flow 1: Workbench Development Session

    User->>Route: GET /lab<br/>Auth: OAuth Token
    Route->>OAuth: Validate OAuth Token<br/>TLS 1.2+ Terminated
    OAuth->>Notebook: Forward Request<br/>HTTP (internal)<br/>Auth: Notebook Token
    Notebook-->>OAuth: Jupyter Lab UI
    OAuth-->>Route: Response
    Route-->>User: HTML/JS Response

    User->>Route: POST /api/kernels<br/>Execute Code
    Route->>OAuth: Forward
    OAuth->>Notebook: Execute Request<br/>Notebook Token

    Note over Notebook,PyPI: Install Python Package
    Notebook->>PyPI: GET /simple/package<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>No Auth
    PyPI-->>Notebook: Package Artifact

    Note over Notebook,S3: Access Training Data
    Notebook->>S3: GET /bucket/dataset.csv<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: AWS IAM
    S3-->>Notebook: Dataset File

    Note over Notebook,Git: Clone Repository
    Notebook->>Git: git clone<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: SSH Key/Token
    Git-->>Notebook: Repository Contents

    Notebook-->>OAuth: Execution Results
    OAuth-->>Route: Results
    Route-->>User: JSON Response

    Note over User,Git: Flow 2: Pipeline Runtime Execution

    participant DSP as DSP Orchestrator
    participant Runtime as Runtime Pod
    participant ModelReg as Model Registry API<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    DSP->>Runtime: Execute Pipeline Step<br/>Kubernetes Exec
    Runtime->>S3: GET /artifacts/model.pkl<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: AWS IAM
    S3-->>Runtime: Model Artifacts
    Runtime->>ModelReg: POST /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/registered_models<br/>HTTP<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    ModelReg-->>Runtime: Model Registered
    Runtime-->>DSP: Step Complete
